content: Chapter 1 Confessions of a Crusty, Crotchety, Cantankerous,  Contrarian, Communist Casualty of Cancel Culture Are you now or have you ever been...? What’s new about cancel culture?  Not as much as it might appear; but not so little either. Cancel culture is as old as culture itself. Every society establishes boundaries of what’s acceptable. If one finds, or places, oneself on the wrong side of them, one gets cancelled. The mechanisms can be subtle—a_ polite rejection letter after submitting a “controversial” article to a scholarly publication—or quite brutal—a stint in a re- education camp or an assassination. Julien Benda, in La Trahison des Clercs (The Treason of the Intellectuals), posited that, if you’re faithful to the values of Truth and Justice, it must inevitably come to pass that you'll be ostracized—or, in the current idiom, “cancelled”—by society: “A clerk who is popular with the laymen is a traitor to his office.” He gestured to Socrates and Jesus.4 A true clerk, according to Benda, accepts Jesus’ dictum: “My Kingdom is not of this world.” Had Benda lived longer, he could have added to his martyrs’ pantheon Malcolm X and Martin Luther King, both of whom, it is now forgotten, were reviled at the time of their respective assassinations. Right after Malcolm X’s death, the New York Times editorialized that “the world he saw through those horn-rimmed glasses of his was distorted and dark. But he made it darker still with his exaltation of fanaticism. Yesterday someone came out of that darkness that he spawned, and killed him.” Who would’ve thunk the outré woke Times cancelled Malcolm  X on his deathbed? When Martin Luther King spoke out

title: chariot voicelines TODO
content:
DIALOGUE

ASSISTANT

> Appointed: "I'm here, I'm here! Whaddya need, Doc?" > Default 1: "The cool morning air is perfect for running in! C'mon, you gotta feel it on your skin. That's what it means to be free." > Default 2: "My sword is too impractical? Ah, yeah, it's true that it really can't cut mountains. Still, gotta take pride in what you have left, right?" > Default 3: "When I was a kid, I thought those pictures of chariots in Minos and Siracusa were like, the coolest thing. S'why I chose this code name, 'Chariot'- They're basically unstoppable, right? And I'm uh, y'know, pretty unstoppable, too!" > Promotion 1: "You know, a few Operators here wear masks. It's just another piece of clothing for them- a part of them that can't be separated from them. Whether it's a friend or a way to cover up a wound... A lot of people wear masks, if it's like that, huh? Well, not me, of course!" > Promotion 2: "What does it mean, being a hero? What more must I do, until I might adopt such a title? ...Ah, Doctor. Sorry. It's just that- I was lost in my own thoughts. There's a question I have to answer one day. It's for someone very important to me." > 40% Trust: "Rhodes Island isn't just about helping with the Oripathy in people's bodies, huh? They're even helping with the Oripathy in people's hearts and minds, too. Even if we can't get rid of Oripathy for good, the Infected should be given the right to live, not just be allowed to survive." > 100% Trust: "At night, it's not so cold like Kazimierz. The wind isn't as strong, and even if I don't know everyone here, they won't treat me like I don't exist... Like I'm not a person at all." > 200% Trust: "Broken things can be so beautiful... What was once 'perfect' and 'whole', now becomes irreparably flawed. Even if pieced back together, it will still show those cracks..." > Greeting: "Doc! Are we going yet?" > Idle: "...Just what goes on in that head of yours?"

OPERATOR

> Onboard: "Oh, you're the Doctor? Uh, pleasure to meet you. Operator Chariot, reporting in. You give me a task, I'll do it. As long as I can stay!" > Watching Battle Record: "Ah, so it's like that, huh. I understand everything now..." > Promotion 1: "Whoa, Doc. I'M promoted? Uh, ahah, that really ain't necessary... And I don't get a say in this?!" > Promotion 2: "We have to keep moving towards the tomorrow that we seek. Doctor, you believe in me, so I will believe in you. I will run with you, towards that future you seek." > Added to Squad: "C'mon, c'mon! Let's get goin', already." > Added as Squad Leader: "Huh? Me? Leader? ...Alright, then! Let's uh, let's mosey." > Assigned to Facility: "Yep, I'm here. Won't slack off this time... yet." > Tap: "Wh-! Please... um, please don't touch me so suddenly..." > Trust Tap: "Oh, hey Doc... Um, how long have you been there?" > Titles: "ARK-nights!"

COMBAT

> Depart: "Alrighty! Let's see this quest through." > Wave Start: "Hostiles incoming! Lemme at 'em!" > Deploy 1: "Coming in hot!" > Deploy 2: "I'm here, I'm here!" > Selected 1: "Who's the beatdown...?" > Selected 2: "No standing pat. Let's go already!" > Using a Skill 1: "I'm the beatdown!" > Using a Skill 2: "Double down!" > Using a Skill 3: "Time to split!" > Using a Skill 4: "Alright! All-in!" > 4-star Result: "Nice. Scratch down another big win for us in the books." > 3-star Result: "Hey, great job, Doc. I'm pretty good, huh?" > 2-star Result: "If they come back, we'll get 'em then... I hope they don't come back." > Failure: "Everyone, run! Get going! I'll... I'll pull my weight, right here, right now. I'll hold them off while you run, so go...!"
